<collectingCountry box="[497,590,764,790]" name="Panama" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Panama</collectingCountry>
(Chiriqui).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Natural history.—No information is available on natural history of this species. The habitat along the Continental Divide Trail near the La 
<collectingCountry box="[896,987,844,870]" name="Wallis and Futuna" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fortuna</collectingCountry>
Dam is a wet ridgetop cloud forest. Given the plant associations of its close relatives 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1146,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Metamasius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bromeliadicola">
<emphasis box="[931,1146,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">M. bromeliadicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Metamasius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrilineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">M. quadrilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is suspected that this species also is associated with bromeliads.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[264,1324,284,1070]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
